<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="563" type="conclusions">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Conclusions.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="563">
The examination of the holotype and of the aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 5–9" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 5 - 9. Median lobe of the aedeagi of 5 Bembidion (Peryphanes) sanatum Bates, 1883, holotype (NHMUK), 1.55 mm 6 B. (P.) dostali Kirschenhofer, 1984, paratype (NHMW), 1.53 mm 7 B. (P.) lulinense Habu, 1973 (drawing from Habu 1973), 1.41 mm 8 Bembidion (Peryphus) psuchrum Andrewes, 1935, holotype (NHMUK), 0.91 mm 9 Bembidion (Plataphus) pseudolucillum Netolitzky, paratype (NHMW), 0.80 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1044.62593.figures5-9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/555047" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">9</figureCitation>
) shows that the species belongs to subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Plataphus)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Plataphus">Bembidion Plataphus</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1864. The doubts regarding the systematic position of the species are due to its pronotal convexity, more evident than in other species of the subgenus. We added to all the non-type specimens the following label: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" baseAuthorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Plataphus) pseudolucillum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudolucillum" subGenus="Plataphus">Bembidion (Plataphus) pseudolucillum</taxonomicName>
Net. - det. Neri and Toledano 2020. The species length varies from 3.6 to 4.7 mm, the aedeagus from 0.75 to 0.84 mm.
</paragraph>
